---

<section class="px-6 md:px-10 py-32 md:py-48 bg-[color:var(--color-ink)] text-[color:var(--color-paper)] overflow-hidden relative" data-cursor-mode="dark">
  <!-- Decorative oversized number -->
  <div class="pointer-events-none select-none absolute -bottom-20 md:-bottom-32 -right-10 serif text-[28vw] md:text-[18vw] leading-none text-white/[0.04]">
    01
  </div>

  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-[1280px]">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/40 mb-10 reveal">
      A short manifesto
    </div>

    <h2 class="serif text-[44px] leading-[1.05] sm:text-7xl md:text-[120px] md:leading-[0.96] tracking-[-0.025em] text-balance">
      <span class="block split">The interfaces that get used</span>
      <span class="block split"><em class="italic text-white/60">are the ones</em> that get out</span>
      <span class="block split">of the way. <em class="italic text-white/60">My job</em> is to get</span>
      <span class="block split">out of the way, beautifully.</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8">
      <div class="md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 reveal">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/65">
          I design with restraint. I edit more than I add. The portfolio below
          is a body of work that took ten years to look this quiet — every
          screen the residue of a hundred decisions you'll never see.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
